The paper focuses on deep hashing methods for large-scale Web media search, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of Generative Adversarial Network (GAN), which is a popular topic in both computer vision and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper deals with data augmentation and semi-supervised learning, which are also relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM).
